{
  "dev": {
    "JIRA_BASE_URL": "https://your-org.atlassian.net",
    "JIRA_EMAIL": "you@example.com",
    "JIRA_API_TOKEN": "your-api-token",
    "JIRA_BASIC_AUTH": "base64-ENCODED-string-of-`you@example.com:your-api-token`"
  }
}

// How to use:
// 1) Copy this file to either http-client.env.json or http-client.private.env.json (preferred) at the repo root.
// 2) Replace values for your environment. Compute JIRA_BASIC_AUTH by base64 encoding "<email>:<api-token>".
//    Examples:
//      macOS/Linux:  echo -n "you@example.com:your-api-token" | base64
//      PowerShell:   [Convert]::ToBase64String([Text.Encoding]::ASCII.GetBytes("you@example.com:your-api-token"))
// 3) In JetBrains IDE, select the environment (e.g., dev) when running requests from .http files.
